column24: Repairing the infrastructure to resist earthquakes and natural disasters and providing decent housing for villages and mountainous areas that live in mud houses, as information has been found about the areas that build their houses from mud. This is due to the fact that the authorities prevent them from urban construction and building with stone, but are forced to build them with mud. To attract tourists, since the purpose of tourists to visit these areas is to see the residents who live in houses made of mud and dirt, so the residents are prevented from urban construction (Al-Sass and Lebrik) in order to attract foreign tourism. This is what we need in Morocco, as well as providing decent education and hospitals capable of accommodating victims. Natural disasters and so on make it difficult to treat patients with high technologies, as in public hospitals you find that even a scanner or radio is not available.

Takdisht is one of the villages of the Argana community in the Taroudant province. People there live in very difficult conditions, with homes damaged by serious cracks and cracks, and residents find themselves forced to stay out in the open in order to maintain their safety. We hope that the responsible authorities will respond to the call of these residents by conducting inspections and providing support and assistance as soon as possible.

column26: Qashish area - Medina Community - Marrakesh Prefecture
column31:
Peace and mercy of God.
Thank you for this noble humanitarian initiative. I work at Almohad Rehabilitation Secondary School, which is located in the Qashish area of â€‹â€‹the Medina community in Marrakesh, which suffers from social fragility. As a result of this earthquake, many families were affected after their homes collapsed or after their homes became destined to collapse, as some of them are currently living in poverty. He sleeps in the shelter established by the Collective Council of the City of Marrakesh in the August 20 stadium in the Qashish area. Some of them sleep in tents on the sidewalk adjacent to the wall of the ancient city, and some of them take refuge with their relatives. In our high school, we launched a donation initiative to extend a helping hand to them, and I suggested to my high school classmates to research About a way to purchase school supplies since we are still in the school entry period and studies have resumed. I knocked on the doors of some associations for this purpose, but I have not received any response yet. I hope that you will respond to my request, and I thank you very much.

column31:
The situation is dire. There are 3 villages in the Skoura community, Ouarzazate province, that are severely damaged. More than half of the residents of these villages live outside their homes, whether in tents or in the open, because the houses have partially fallen or been exposed to serious damage and are at risk of collapsing at any moment, which constitutes a hideout for the residents despite the hunger that has arisen. Local associations are able to provide collective tents, but they remain insufficient. Unfortunately, until now, no aid has arrived to these circles. Except this morning, some aid arrived from the internal authority, but it is very little.
The main problem that worries the residents is primarily the problem of shelter

column26: The community of the people of Tefnut and Amoum from Totaghran roundabout
column31:
What can I say? There is no power nor strength except with God, the Most High, the Great. Elderly men, women and children living with weak capabilities. Mothers crying with tears of heartbreak. Blood at the loss of loved ones. Entire families have passed away. We belong to God and to Him we shall return.
 Material and human losses due to the earthquake. Most of the houses are demolished and others are subject to demolition. We ask philanthropists and people of good conscience to provide a helping hand to those in need, because the officials in this department are in a deep slumber.
 I have never seen such a scene in my life that breaks the heart. Praise be to Him who pardoned us from what He afflicted them with and favored us over many of those He created.

column31: This roundabout has not received any help since the beginning of the earthquake until now, and there are several dead people who have not been recovered from under the rubble. The small group that survived did not receive any aid or the intervention of the local authorities. They are demanding clothing, food, tents, and medical teams to come to the affected people and provide assistance. They are sleeping in the mountains, as their homes have also been destroyed. The aid that comes to them meets the circles on the road, and they have not received any aid. Knowing that they have young children who suffer in this cold without cover or clothes. The guide to goodness is like the one who does it.

column27: Al-Zawiyat al-Nahli community center is on Route 212 leading to Amantanot. You ask via Ehsayniten Road, which leads to the left, which leads to Targunt, Tebia, etc.
column31:
People need clothes and tents (shelter), especially for women and children, because houses collapsed and people lost everything, especially in these roundabouts: (Tabia roundabout, Boukhalef roundabout, Targount roundabout, Katous roundabout, Talouine roundabout, Agne roundabout, Emi and Gendarmerie roundabout, Arkrakne roundabout, Wejdan roundabout. (Aufin roundabout, Amasin roundabout, Boukhalef roundabout). The majority of these roundabouts have had their homes destroyed and people are living in the open without shelter.
Please send aid and make sure that it reaches the place. There is a road that leads to these circles near the headquarters of the Zawiya al-Nahli community, on the left at the entrance from Marrakesh on Route 212, and on the right at the entrance from Imnanot.

column31:
â€œMy motherâ€™s roundabout and the sword of money, Chishawaâ€
This roundabout has not received any help since the beginning of the earthquake until now, and there are several dead people who have not been recovered from under the rubble. The small group that survived did not receive any aid or the intervention of the local authorities. They are demanding clothing, food, tents, and medical teams to rescue the affected people and provide assistance. They are sleeping in the mountains as their homes have been destroyed, and the aid that comes to them meets the circles on the road, and they have not received any aid. Knowing that they have young children suffering in this cold without cover or clothes, they are in dire need of help.
 This is the number of one of those affected by this roundabout: 0618501751.
 The guide to goodness is like the one who does it.

column26: Ikli roundabout, Ikli community, Ikli leadership
column31:
A large percentage of people have become their homes in the open air. Praise be to God, there are no deaths, but there are some people whose homes have been completely destroyed, others are ready to collapse at any moment and are uninhabitable, and the rest of the buildings are all torn apart. People are in dire need of any assistance, especially food, other than water, because it is available. Decent tents protect people until the Lord comes, because most of them are homeless and their social condition is very deteriorating, preventing them from building new homes without the help of benefactors. We have received some aid, thank God, but it remains very small compared to the needs of the affected population.
This video shows some of the damage to the country

Their houses were torn from the inside, and some of them had fallen. They were built of mud. They are spending the night outdoors now. None of them died, thank God.
They do not ask for anything other than food items. They did not receive any of them due to people not paying attention to them.
